---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Outreach" description="Public engagement: the Hannah Arendt Institute, public lectures, the PACT School Tour, and media appearances.">

  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Outreach</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        As a publicly funded researcher, I believe research should serve the broader society. Through public lectures, school visits, media engagement, 
        and my work with the Hannah Arendt Institute, I try to make academic knowledge about polarisation and democracy accessible and actionable.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TWO CARDS: HAI + PUBLIC TALKS -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="project-grid">
        <div class="project-card" style="padding: 1.25rem;">
          <p class="project-card__label">Hannah Arendt Instituut</p>
          <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.7;">
            As a senior academic fellow at the <a href="https://hannah-arendt.institute/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hannah Arendt Institute</a> for diversity, urbanity, and citizenship, I am part of the <a href="https://hannah-arendt.institute/samenwerken/onderzoeker/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">academic team</a> where I help organise academic and public events, bring expertise and insights to the Institute, and gain access to their network. The HAI bridges scientific knowledge with the practices of policymakers, organisations, and citizens — a mission I am proud to contribute to.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="project-card" style="padding: 1.25rem;">
          <p class="project-card__label">Public talks</p>
          <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.7;">
            I regularly give public lectures, panel discussions, and school visits on polarisation, democracy, and critical thinking. This includes guest lectures for the <a href="https://www.vub.be/nl/nieuws/vub-pact-school-tour-caroline-pauwels-atheneum-polarisatie" target="_blank" rel="noopener">VUB PACT School Tour</a> (Caroline Pauwels Academy of Critical Thinking), presentations at public events via the Hannah Arendt Institute, and the <a href="https://checkfirst.network/event/lunch-lecture-with-kamil-bernaerts/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">EDMO BELUX Lunch Lecture</a> series. Interested in inviting me? <a href="/contact/">Get in touch</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- IN THE MEDIA -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section__label">In the media</p>
      <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; max-width: 680px;">
        My research on institutional design, polarisation, and democracy has been covered in Belgian and international media.
      </p>

      <div class="pub-item">
        <div>
          <p class="pub-title">Onderzoek VUB: Belgische democratie minder gevoelig voor polarisering</p>
          <p class="pub-authors"><a href="https://www.knack.be/nieuws/belgie/politiek/onderzoek-vub-belgische-democratie-minder-gevoelig-voor-polarisering/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Knack</a></p>
        </div>
        <div class="pub-meta"><p class="pub-year">2022</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="pub-item">
        <div>
          <p class="pub-title">VUB: Belgische democratie is minder gevoelig aan polarisering</p>
          <p class="pub-authors"><a href="https://www.hln.be/binnenland/vub-belgische-democratie-is-minder-gevoelig-aan-polarisering~a19058f5/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Het Laatste Nieuws</a></p>
        </div>
        <div class="pub-meta"><p class="pub-year">2022</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="pub-item">
        <div>
          <p class="pub-title">Notre système politique belge divise moins la société en deux</p>
          <p class="pub-authors"><a href="https://www.rtbf.be/article/notre-systeme-politique-belge-divise-moins-la-societe-en-deux-que-les-democraties-majoritaires-selon-une-these-de-la-vub-11120434" target="_blank" rel="noopener">RTBF</a></p>
        </div>
        <div class="pub-meta"><p class="pub-year">2022</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="pub-item">
        <div>
          <p class="pub-title">Onderzoek VUB: Belgische democratie minder gevoelig voor polarisering</p>
          <p class="pub-authors"><a href="https://www.bruzz.be/samenleving/onderzoek-vub-belgische-democratie-minder-gevoelig-voor-polarisering-2022-12-09" target="_blank" rel="noopener">BRUZZ</a></p>
        </div>
        <div class="pub-meta"><p class="pub-year">2022</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="pub-item">
        <div>
          <p class="pub-title">La démocratie belge moins sensible à la polarisation</p>
          <p class="pub-authors"><a href="https://www.lalibre.be/belgique/societe/2022/12/09/la-democratie-belge-moins-sensible-a-la-polarisation-MQ7FYPXDKVFLJO7TVFDED2L3QA/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">La Libre Belgique</a></p>
        </div>
        <div class="pub-meta"><p class="pub-year">2022</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="pub-item">
